The paper discusses approximation algorithms for a graph optimization problem, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of the primal-dual scheme and the analysis of approximation ratios suggest that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The focus on optimization and approximation also suggests that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the mention of running time suggests that it could belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
